doc.after: Giraffes have an unusually long lifespan compared to other ruminants,[67] up to 25 years in the wild.[17] Because of their size, eyesight and powerful kicks, adult giraffes are usually not subject to predation.[25] However, they can fall prey to lions and are regular prey for them in Kruger National Park.[68] Nile crocodiles can also be a threat to giraffes when they bend down to drink.[32]:31 Calves are much more vulnerable than adults, and are additionally preyed on by leopards, spotted hyenas and wild dogs.[15] A quarter to a half of giraffe calves reach adulthood.
